episodes.title: Are You There Shim? It's Me, Ian.
episodes.plot: Frank gets into trouble with the Hopkins Academy PTA. Fiona struggles with her decision to bail Ian out of jail, while he continues his Gay Jesus antics inside. Lip juggles taking care of Xan with a potential romance.

episodes.title: Mo White!
episodes.plot: Fiona pursues a risky investment opportunity. Frank discovers the financial incentives of local politics. Carl bolsters his West Point application in unexpected ways. Ian is overwhelmed by the growth of the Gay Jesus movement.

episodes.title: Weirdo Gallagher Vortex
episodes.plot: Frank faces obstacles in his new role. Fiona prepares to close her real estate deal. Carl enlists V to help him get a recommendation from a congressman. Xan has a medical emergency. Ian embarks on a spiritual journey.

episodes.title: Do Right, Vote White!
episodes.plot: Election day puts Frank and Fiona in a head-to-head battle as they each try to round up votes for their candidates. Lip makes a choice about Xan's future. With his trial looming, Ian struggles to decide how to plead. 100th episode.

episodes.title: Black-Haired Ginger
episodes.plot: Frank's new liver medication comes with tragic side effects. Ian tries to get away from Fiona's hovering. Lip has to keep himself occupied during a day of temptation. Carl makes a connection at a West Point mixer.

episodes.title: Face It, You're Gorgeous
episodes.plot: Frank employs Liam to help him chase down a romantic connection and Fiona struggles to keep up with the demands of her new investment as Ford pushes her to get serious about their relationship.

episodes.title: Down Like the Titanic
episodes.plot: Debbie finds Fiona at a low point and helps her pick up the pieces as Fiona continues to face pressure from Max Whitford on her investment hubris. Frank enjoys the honeymoon period of his relationship with Ingrid.

episodes.title: The Apple Doesn't Fall Far From the Alibi
episodes.plot: Fiona's downward spiral continues and Debbie steps in to pick up the slack at the Gallagher house. Ingrid ropes Frank into fulfilling her lifelong dream. Tami shows Lip a different version of adulthood.

episodes.title: BOOOOOOOOOOOONE!
episodes.plot: Frank searches for ways to finance Ingrid's vision for their future together. Fiona's anger issues cause problems at Patsy's. Lip is forced to confront his real feelings for Tami.

episodes.title: Los Diablos!
episodes.plot: Frank meets his match in a fellow participant in the Hobo Loco competition. Fiona has a dark encounter at Patsy's that scares her into cleaning up her act. Debbie throws herself into home improvements as she gets closer with Kelly.

episodes.title: The Hobo Games
episodes.plot: The finals of the Hobo Games have arrived, and Frank faces off against his friend and greatest opponent. Lip prepares to officially adopt Xan, but his plans collide with Fiona's partying. Debbie develops feelings for someone surprising.

episodes.title: You'll Know the Bottom When You Hit It
episodes.plot: When a blackout hits the South Side, Kevin and Veronica come up with a plan to bring the neighborhood together. Carl grows suspicious of Debbie's attempts to get closer with Kelly. Fiona receives guidance from an unexpected person.

episodes.title: Lost
episodes.plot: Frank's injury gets in the way of everyone's plans as Fiona attempts to get her life back on track and Lip grows frustrated with his relationship with Tami. Carl gets some bad news about his future, and Debbie finally makes a move on Kelly.

episodes.title: Found
episodes.plot: As the Gallaghers decide what to do with a bedridden Frank, Fiona has to make a decision about her future. Carl and Debbie share their heartbreak together. Lip has to deal with a distressed Tami.
